@{par}include it here, as there are a few idiots out there who might abuse it.
@{par}
@{par}Charity registration number 1035774
@{par}
@{par}Patrons:
@{par}@{fg fill}    Dame Judi Dench,
@{par}    Lindsay Duncan,
@{par}    Geraldine James,
@{par}    Griff Rhys Jones,
@{par}    John Gordon Sinclair.@{fg text}
@{par}
@{par}Trustees:
@{par}    @{fg fill}A. Demetriades,
@{par}    A. Berkeley,
@{par}    M. Janota Bzowski,
@{par}    S. Pickford,
@{par}    G. Walker,
@{par}    M. Johnson,
@{par}    F. Capone.@{fg text}
@{par}
@{par}Consultants:
@{par}    @{fg fill}M. Fox THE TAVISTOCK CLINIC,
@{par}    M. Martin LEGAL ADVISER,
@{par}    A. Heywood A.C.A,
@{par}    S. Kasabova CAMDEN L.E.A.@{fg text}
@{par}
@{par}    The address is up there, so go on, donate!
@{par}    If you think you can offer something other than money, write!
@{par}
@{par}    I want to say a huge thanks to anyone who does donate some money.
@{par}
@{par}    Thanks for at least reading this... and sorry for any mistakes in
@{par}    the above text - my typing can go a bit haywire sometimes!!

@ENDNODE
@NODE Intro "DOpusFuncs - Introduction"

@{par}The purpose behind @{fg fill}DOpusFuncs@{fg text} is to provide you with some features which
are currently @{b}missing@{ub} from @{fg fill}DOpus5@{fg text}.
@{par}
@{par}@{fg fill}DOpusFuncs@{fg text} started as a conversion of the @{fg shine}DirToDest@{fg text}, @{fg shine}ParentToDest@{fg text},
@{fg shine}Same @{fg text}(@{fg shine}Clone@{fg text}), @{fg shine}WinCopy@{fg text}, and @{fg shine}WinSwap @{fg fill}Directory Opus 5@{fg text} scripts. I was annoyed
with how long the scripts took to do their job, so I converted them to
assembler.
@{par}
@{par}At the moment, @{fg fill}DOpusFuncs@{fg text} provides you with these extra commands:
@{par}
@{par}@{fg fill}1)@{fg text} @{b}Read@{ub} the @{b}selected directory@{ub} into an existing or new lister, without
@{par}   having to drag'n'drop it.
@{par}@{fg fill}2)@{fg text} Read a lister's @{b}parent@{ub} directory into a lister.
@{par}@{fg fill}3)@{fg text} @{b}Clone@{ub} a lister.
@{par}@{fg fill}4)@{fg text} @{b}Swap@{ub} two listers.
@{par}@{fg fill}5)@{fg text} Put filenames, lister paths, etc. in the @{b}clipboard@{ub}.
@{par}@{fg fill}6)@{fg text} @{b}Close@{ub} or @{b}iconify all@{ub} listers.
@{par}

@{par}Read the @{" usage " LINK Usage} node to see exactly what it can do.

@ENDNODE
@NODE Requirements "DOpusFuncs - Requirements"

@{par}See also: @{" Known Bugs " LINK Future}
@{par}
@{par}This program should run on any Amiga with AmigaOS 2 or above.
@{par}
@{par}Of course, you also need @{fg shine}Directory Opus 5@{fg text} (version @{b}5.5@{ub} or above).
@{par}
@{par}This @{fg fill}AmigaGuide@{fg text} takes advantage of some of the extra features of the
@{fg fill}OS3.1 amigaguide.datatype@{fg text}, such as @{fg fill}SmartWrap@{fg text}, @{fg fill}WordWrap@{fg text}, @{fg fill}Colour@{fg text}, and @{fg fill}Styles@{fg text}.
@{fg fill}OS3.0@{fg text} users should get everything apart from the @{fg fill}SmartWrapping@{fg text}, and @{fg fill}OS2@{fg text} 
users should still see the same text, just not as @{bg shine}p@{bg fill}r@{bg shine}e@{bg fill}t@{bg shine}t@{bg fill}y@{bg back}.

@ENDNODE
