@NODE "CheckGuide" "CheckGuide by Eddy Carroll"

@{par}          @{fg shine}CheckGuide 1.0 -- Checks AmigaGuide files for common errors
@{par}
@{par}             by Eddy Carroll, September 1994. Freely distributable.@{fg text}
@{par}
@{par}Introduction
@{par}
@{par}If you've ever tried creating even a modestly sized AmigaGuide file by hand,
@{par}you'll have discovered that it can be quite difficult to keep track of all the
@{par}various links and cross references. As your help file gets larger, it gets
@{par}increasingly harder to ensure that you have remembered to reference all the
@{par}nodes in the file from at least one place, and haven't left any unresolved
@{par}links.
@{par}
@{par}CheckGuide is a simple utility that can detect several common errors in
@{par}AmigaGuide files. The errors it can detect are:
@{par}
@{par}Ę Extra plain text between an \@ENDNODE and \@NODE (AmigaGuide won't allow such
@{par}  text to ever be displayed)
@{par}
@{par}Ę Nodes that are defined but not referenced from any other node. Unless your
@{par}  program directly instructs AmigaGuide to access such nodes, the user won't
@{par}  easily be able to access them.
@{par}
@{par}Ę Links to help nodes that aren't defined within the file.
@{par}
@{par}Ę Open braces with no preceding \@ character (usually a simple typo).
@{par}
@{par}Ę \@{" Button "} constructs with no LINK command (an easy mistake to make if
@{par}  you're entering a lot of them).
@{par}
@{par}All of these options can be selectively enabled or disabled.
@{par}
@{par}        @{fg shine}CheckGuide was used in the creation of @{b}THIS@{ub} document!@{fg text}

@ENDNODE
@NODE Installation "DOpusFuncs - Installation"

@{par}See also: @{" Usage " LINK Usage}
@{par}          @{" Examples " LINK Examples}
@{par}
@{par}@{b}NOTE:@{ub} This is just a @{u}suggestion@{uu} of how to install it. You can do with it
@{par}      what you want.
@{par}
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} Make sure the @{fg fill}"P"@{fg text} bit is set as this program is @{fg shine}'Pure'@{fg text} and may be made
@{par}  @{b}resident@{ub} @{fg fill}(see below)@{fg text}.
@{par}@{fg fill}>@{fg text} @{bg fill} Protect DOpusFuncs +P @{bg back}
@{par}
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} Copy the main file to @{fg fill}DOpus5:c/@{fg text}
@{par}@{fg fill}>@{fg text} @{bg fill} Copy DOpusFuncs DOpus5:c/ @{bg back}
@{par}
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} Copy the AmigaGuide to @{fg fill}DOpus5:Help/@{fg text}
@{par}@{fg fill}>@{fg text} @{bg fill} Copy DOpusFuncs.guide DOpus5:Help/ @{bg back}
@{par}
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} Read the @{" usage " LINK Usage} and @{" examples " LINK Examples} sections and set up whatever buttons you
@{par}  like.
@{par}
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} If you want to make the command @{b}resident@{ub} (to save loading time), add this
@{par}  line to your @{fg fill}S:User-Startup@{fg text}...
@{par}@{fg fill}>@{fg text} @{bg fill} Resident DOpus5:c/DOpusFuncs @{bg back}
@{par}  ...and change all commands to reference @{fg fill}"DOpusFuncs"@{fg text} instead of
@{par}  @{fg fill}"DOpus5:c/DOpusFuncs"@{fg text}.

@ENDNODE
@NODE Usage "DOpusFuncs - Usage"

@{par}See also: @{" Installation " LINK Installation}
@{par}          @{" Examples " LINK Examples}
@{par}
@{par}The @{fg fill}DOpusFuncs@{fg text} command takes the following command-line parameters:
@{par}
@{par}@{fg shine}Mandatory:@{fg text}
@{par} @{" RexxPort   " LINK U_RexxPort}  Specify the DOpus5 @{b}ARexx port@{ub}.
@{par}@{fg shine}Action selection:@{fg text}
@{par} @{" ClipEntry  " LINK U_ClipEntry}  Copy filenames etc. to @{b}clipboard@{ub}.
@{par} @{" ScanParent " LINK U_ScanParent}  @{fg fill}Switch:@{fg text} Open the @{b}parent@{ub} of the source lister.
@{par} @{" WinCopy    " LINK U_WinCopy}  @{fg fill}Switch:@{fg text} @{b}Copy@{ub} the source lister.
@{par} @{" WinSwap    " LINK U_WinSwap}  @{fg fill}Switch:@{fg text} @{b}Swap@{ub} source and destination listers.
@{par} @{" PathSwap   " LINK U_PathSwap}  @{fg fill}Switch:@{fg text} @{b}Swap@{ub} source and destination listers(!).
@{par} @{" LCloseAll  " LINK U_LCloseAll}  @{fg fill}Switch:@{fg text} @{b}Close all@{ub} listers.
@{par} @{" LIconAll   " LINK U_LIconAll}  @{fg fill}Switch:@{fg text} @{b}Iconify all@{ub} listers.
@{par}@{fg shine}Options:@{fg text}
@{par} @{" LineClip   " LINK U_LineClip}  @{fg fill}Switch:@{fg text} Put clipped filenames on separate lines.
@{par} @{" New        " LINK U_New}  @{fg fill}Switch:@{fg text} Force the openning of a new lister.
@{par} @{" NewPos     " LINK U_NewPos}  Specify the position of any new listers.
@{par}
@{par}@{fg shine}@{u}ReadArgs() Template:@{uu}@{fg text}
@{par}
@{par}RP=REXXPORT/A, CLIPENTRY/K/M, SCANPARENT/S, WINCOPY/S, WINSWAP/S,
LCLOSEALL/S, LICONALL/S, NEW/S, NEWPOS/K, LINECLIP/S
@{par}
@{par}
@{par}@{fg shine}Well I've been to Hastings,
@{par}And I've been to Brighton,
@{par}I've been to Eastborn, too
@{par}So what, So what? ...@{fg text}

@ENDNODE
@NODE U_RexxPort "DOpusFuncs - Usage, RexxPort"

@{par}See also: @{" Examples " LINK Examples}
@{par}
@{par}Alias: @{fg fill}"RP"@{fg text}
@{par}
@{par}@{fg fill}RexxPort@{fg text} is a @{b}mandatory keyword@{ub} with which you specify the name of DOpus5's
ARexx port. This should @{b}always@{ub} be done using the @{fg shine}{Qp}@{fg text} sequence within
the DOpus5 function editor, as shown in all of the @{" examples " LINK Examples}.
@{par}
@{par}@{b}NOTE:@{ub} Port names are @{u}case-sensitive@{uu}.

@ENDNODE
@NODE U_ClipEntry "DOpusFuncs - Usage, ClipEntry"
@{par}See also: @{" Examples " LINK Examples}
@{par}          @{" LineClip " LINK U_LineClip}
@{par}>>>>>>>>> @{" Known Bugs " LINK Future}
@{par}
@{par}The @{fg fill}ClipEntry@{fg text} @{b}keyword@{ub} takes @{b}all@{ub} words from the command-line which are not
part of other arguments and puts them in the @{fg fill}clipboard@{fg text} as @{b}one@{ub} string. When
used on a DOpus5 button with the @{fg shine}{}@{fg text} commands you can do useful things such
as copy the names of all selected files to the clipboard.
@{par}
@{par}DOpus5.5 has internal filename-clip support (Amiga-C and Amiga-Shift-C),
yet the ClipEntry function is still useful for other things.
@{par}
@{par}It is easy to setup a toolbar button which clips the name of any icon
dropped on to it. You can even use DOpusFuncs to put text into the
clipboard independently of DOpus.
@{par}
@{par}Quotes will be placed around any sub-strings with spaces in, provided you
have left the @{fg fill}"No file quote"@{fg text} switch in Opus @{b}off@{ub}.
@{par}
@{par}Note: Due to AmigaDOS limitations and the way in which DOpusFuncs and
@{par}      DOpus5 interract, you are limited to clipping around 450 characters
@{par}      at a time. I could remove this limitation but only at the expense
@{par}      of only being able to clip filenames from Opus which is pointless as
@{par}      this is done internally already.
@{par}
@{par}Have a look at the @{" examples " LINK Examples} section to see some of the things it can
do.

@ENDNODE
@NODE U_LineClip "DOpusFuncs - Usage, LineClip"

@{par}See also: @{" Examples " LINK Examples}
@{par}          @{" ClipEntry " LINK U_ClipEntry}
@{par}
@{par}The @{fg fill}LineClip@{fg text} @{b}switch@{ub} changes the behaviour of @{" ClipEntry " LINK U_ClipEntry} when multiple
strings are being clipped. Normally, all strings are separated by spaces
and put on a single line. This switch causes each string to appear on
a separate line.
@{par}
@{par}Note: The last line will not have a return at the end.

@ENDNODE
@NODE U_ScanParent "DOpusFuncs - Usage, ScanParent"

@{par}See also: @{" Examples " LINK Examples}
@{par}          @{" New " LINK U_New}
@{par}
@{par}The @{fg fill}ScanParent@{fg text} @{b}switch@{ub} causes the parent directory of the source lister
to be read into the destination lister, if one exists, and a new lister
otherwise.
@{par}
@{par}If the source lister shows the root directory of a volume you will get a
device list.
@{par}
@{par}You can force the parent directory to be read into a new lister with
the @{" New " LINK U_New} switch.

@ENDNODE
@NODE U_WinCopy "DOpusFuncs - Usage, WinCopy"

@{par}See also: @{" Examples " LINK Examples}
@{par}          @{" New " LINK U_New}
@{par}
@{par}
@{par}The @{fg fill}WinCopy@{fg text} @{b}switch@{ub} will read the source lister's path into the destination
lister, if one exists, and into a new lister otherwise.
@{par}
@{par}You can force the path to be read into a new lister with the @{" New " LINK U_New} switch.

@ENDNODE
@NODE U_WinSwap "DOpusFuncs - Usage, WinSwap"

@{par}See also: @{" Examples " LINK Examples}
@{par}          @{" PathSwap " LINK U_PathSwap}
@{par}
@{par}
@{par}The @{fg fill}WinSwap@{fg text} @{b}switch@{ub} swaps around the source and destination listers.
@{par}
@{par}Normally the swap is done by moving the windows themselves, but if one of
the listers is locked in position it will swap their paths instead.
@{par}
@{par}If you would like to swap the contents but not the formats of the two
listers use @{" PathSwap " LINK U_PathSwap} instead.

@ENDNODE
@NODE U_PathSwap "DOpusFuncs - Usage, PathSwap"

@{par}See also: @{" Examples " LINK Examples}
@{par}          @{" WinSwap " LINK U_WinSwap}
@{par}
@{par}
@{par}The @{fg fill}PathSwap@{fg text} @{b}switch@{ub} swaps around the source and destination listers.
@{par}
@{par}Most of the time the @{" WinSwap " LINK U_WinSwap} command is a quicker way of doing this, but
there may be times when your two listers are displaying different types of
information (different path formats) and you only want to swap the contents
of the listers, not the listers themselves. In this case, the PathSwap
command is for you.

@ENDNODE
@NODE U_LCloseAll "DOpusFuncs - Usage, LCloseAll"

@{par}See also: @{" LIconAll " LINK U_LIconAll}
@{par}
@{par}The @{fg fill}LCloseAll@{fg text} @{b}switch@{ub} causes @{b}all listers@{ub} (including iconified ones) to be
@{b}closed@{ub}. Great for cleaning up your Opus screen when you've just finished
doing some complex stuff.

@ENDNODE
@NODE U_LIconAll "DOpusFuncs - Usage, LIconAll"

@{par}See also: @{" LCloseAll " LINK U_LCloseAll}
@{par}
@{par}The @{fg fill}LIconAll@{fg text} @{b}switch@{ub} causes @{b}all listers@{ub} to be @{b}iconified@{ub}. Great for clearing
some space on your Opus screen when one job interrupts another which you
want to continue with afterwards.

@ENDNODE
@NODE U_New "DOpusFuncs - Usage, New"

@{par}See also: @{" NewPos " LINK U_NewPos}
@{par}          @{" ScanParent " LINK U_ScanParent}
@{par}          @{" WinCopy " LINK U_WinCopy}
@{par}
@{par}By default, @{" ScanParent " LINK U_ScanParent} and @{" WinCopy " LINK U_WinCopy} will only create a new lister if
there is no destination lister. The @{fg fill}New@{fg text} @{b}switch@{ub} changes things so that
a new lister is always created.
@{par}
@{par}You can set the new listers position with the @{" NewPos " LINK U_NewPos} keyword.

@ENDNODE
@NODE U_NewPos "DOpusFuncs - Usage, NewPos"

@{par}See also: @{" New " LINK U_New}
@{par}          @{" ScanParent " LINK U_ScanParent}
@{par}          @{" WinCopy " LINK U_WinCopy}
@{par}
@{par}By default, new listers created by DOpusFuncs open under your mouse
pointer with the default size or that snapshotted to the path.
@{par}
@{par}The @{fg fill}NewPos@{fg text} @{b}keyword@{ub} can be used to set a different size and/or position for
new listers openned by @{" ScanParent " LINK U_ScanParent} or @{" WinCopy " LINK U_WinCopy}.
@{par}
@{par}The format is @{fg fill}<x-pos>@{fg text}/@{fg fill}<y-pos>@{fg text}/@{fg fill}<width>@{fg text}/@{fg fill}<height>@{fg text}, e.g. 50/10/100/200
@{par}
@{par}@{b}NOTE: @{ub}Specifying -1/-1/@{fg fill}<w>@{fg text}/@{fg fill}<h>@{fg text} will make the lister open under the mouse.

@ENDNODE
@NODE Examples "DOpusFuncs - Examples"

@{par}See also: @{" Usage " LINK Usage}
@{par}
@{par}Here are some quick examples of how to use the program:
@{par}
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} For a button which @{b}swaps@{ub} the @{fg fill}'source'@{fg text} and @{fg fill}'dest'@{fg text} listers:
@{par}@{fg fill}>@{fg text} @{bg fill} AmigaDOS @{bg back}
@{par}@{fg fill}>@{fg text} @{bg fill} DOpus5:c/DOpusFuncs {Qp} WinSwap @{bg back}
@{par}
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} For a button which @{b}copies@{ub} the @{fg fill}'source'@{fg text} lister to the @{fg fill}'dest'@{fg text} one:
@{par}@{fg fill}>@{fg text} @{bg fill} AmigaDOS @{bg back}
@{par}@{fg fill}>@{fg text} @{bg fill} DOpus5:c/DOpusFuncs {Qp} WinCopy @{bg back}
@{par}  (A new lister will open if there is no 'dest')
@{par}
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} For a button which opens a @{b}clone@{ub} of the @{fg fill}'source'@{fg text} lister:
@{par}@{fg fill}>@{fg text} @{bg fill} AmigaDOS @{bg back}
@{par}@{fg fill}>@{fg text} @{bg fill} DOpus5:c/DOpusFuncs {Qp} WinCopy New @{bg back}
@{par}
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} For a button which reads the @{b}parent@{ub} of the @{fg fill}'source'@{fg text} lister into a new
@{par}  lister:
@{par}@{fg fill}>@{fg text} @{bg fill} AmigaDOS @{bg back}
@{par}@{fg fill}>@{fg text} @{bg fill} DOpus5:c/DOpusFuncs {Qp} ScanParent New @{bg back}
@{par}
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} For a button which @{b}copies@{ub} the @{b}names@{ub} of @{b}all selected entries@{ub} in the
@{par}  @{fg fill}'source'@{fg text} lister to the @{fg fill}clipboard@{fg text}:
@{par}@{fg fill}>@{fg text} @{bg fill} AmigaDOS @{bg back}
@{par}@{fg fill}>@{fg text} @{bg fill} DOpus5:c/DOpusFuncs {Qp} ClipEntry {O} @{bg back}
@{par}
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} For a button which does the @{i}same as above @{ui}but includes the @{b}full path@{ub} of
@{par}  all the files:
@{par}@{fg fill}>@{fg text} @{bg fill} AmigaDOS @{bg back}
@{par}@{fg fill}>@{fg text} @{bg fill} DOpus5:c/DOpusFuncs {Qp} ClipEntry {F} @{bg back}
@{par}
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} For a button which @{b}copies@{ub} the @{b}name@{ub} of the @{b}first selected entry@{ub}:
@{par}@{fg fill}>@{fg text} @{bg fill} AmigaDOS @{bg back}
@{par}@{fg fill}>@{fg text} @{bg fill} DOpus5:c/DOpusFuncs {Qp} ClipEntry {o} @{bg back}
@{par}
@{par}@{fg shine}-@{fg text} If you put one of the three examples above in one of the @{b}left-
@{par}  mousebutton@{ub} functions of a @{b}button bank@{ub} you are able to @{fg shine}drag@{fg text} files and
@{par}  icons from listers and @{fg shine}drop@{fg text} them on the button to have their names put
@{par}  in the clipboard (@{i}of course, @{ui}you can still select-n-click, too).
@{par}
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} For a button which @{b}copies@{ub} the @{b}path@{ub} of the @{fg fill}'source'@{fg text} lister to the
@{par}  @{fg fill}clipboard@{fg text}:
@{par}@{fg fill}>@{fg text} @{bg fill} AmigaDOS @{bg back}
@{par}@{fg fill}>@{fg text} @{bg fill} DOpus5:c/DOpusFuncs {Qp} ClipEntry {s} @{bg back}
@{par}
@{par}@{fg shine}- @{fg text}I hope you get the idea!? @{fg text}Obviously there are many other combinations.
@{par}

@ENDNODE
@NODE History "DOpusFuncs - History"

@{par}See also: @{" Future " LINK Future}
@{par}
@{par}@{b}NOTE:@{ub} Version numbering is in the @{fg shine}<version>@{fg fill}.@{fg shine}<revision>@{fg text} format. This means
@{par}      that version @{fg shine}1.10 @{fg text}(one.ten) is @{b}newer@{ub} than version @{fg shine}1.2 @{fg text}(one.two).
@{par}
@{par}@{u}@{fg shine} v1.1 (Private release) - 19-Aug-1995 @{uu}
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} @{b}First@{ub} release for testing.
@{par}
@{par}@{u}@{fg shine} v1.2 (Private release) - 21-Aug-1995 @{uu}
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} W@{fg fill}r@{fg shine}o@{fg fill}t@{fg text}e @{bg fill}t@{bg shine}h@{bg fill}i@{bg shine}s@{bg back} @{b}A@{ub}@{u}m@{uu}@{b}i@{ub}@{u}g@{uu}@{b}a@{ub}@{u}G@{uu}@{b}u@{ub}@{u}i@{uu}@{b}d@{ub}@{u}e@{uu}.
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} @{b}Fixed@{ub} something in the way that @{fg fill}ARexx@{fg text} messages are sent to @{fg fill}DOpus5@{fg text}.
@{par}  (This shouldn't have caused any problems, but it is done properly now).
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} @{b}Removed@{ub} the @{fg fill}NoReq@{fg text} @{b}switch@{ub} because it was of very little use.
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} @{b}Changed@{ub} the @{fg shine}DeviceList@{fg text} routine to wait for the lister to finish the
@{par}  @{fg shine}DevieList@{fg text} before restoring the orginal @{fg fill}'source'@{fg text} lister. Previously this
@{par}  could happen too quickly and cause the @{fg shine}DeviceList@{fg text} to appear in the
@{par}  wrong lister.
@{par}
@{par}@{u}@{fg shine} v1.3 (Private release) - 27-Aug-1995 @{uu}
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} @{b}Added@{ub} my @{b}new@{ub} @{fg fill}email address@{fg text} to the @{" credits " LINK Credits} node.
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} @{b}Added@{ub} new @{" ClipEntry " LINK U_ClipEntry} @{b}switch@{ub} for the @{fg shine}new function@{fg text}. (@{" Thanks Trevor! " LINK Credits})
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} @{b}Added@{ub} an @{fg fill}icon@{fg text} for this 'guide. (Trevor)
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} @{b}Fixed@{ub} alphabetical-sorting in the @{" credits " LINK Credits} node. (Trevor)
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} @{b}Fixed@{ub} an extra comma (,) in the ReadArgs() template.
@{par}
@{par}@{u}@{fg shine} v1.4 (MWB_DOpus_7.lha release) - 10-Sep-1995 @{uu}
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} @{b}Changed@{ub} @{" ClipEntry " LINK U_ClipEntry}. (Too detailed to list here).
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} @{i}Where useful, @{ui}new listers will open @{b}automatically@{ub} if there isn't a lister
@{par}  of the required type open already (just like @{fg fill}DOpus5's@{fg text} internal commands).
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} @{b}Added@{ub} @{bg fill} NoNew @{bg back} @{b}switch@{ub} to disable the above feature.
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} @{b}Fixed@{ub} some error requesters which were using @{fg fill}EasyRequestArgs()@{fg text} instead
@{par}  of @{fg fill}"dopus request"@{fg text}.
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} @{b}Added@{ub} two new @{" known bugs " LINK Future}, neither of which are my fault. :)
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} @{b}Fixed@{ub} a few node titles which had @{fg fill}"CDOpus"@{fg text} in them.
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} @{b}Updated@{ub} the @{bg fill} NewEdit @{bg back} node.
@{par}
@{par}@{u}@{fg shine} v1.5 - 24-Sep-1995 @{uu}
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} @{b}Changed@{ub} @{" WinSwap " LINK U_WinSwap} and @{" WinCopy " LINK U_WinCopy} not to use the @{fg fill}"lister copy"@{fg text} command because
@{par}  it does not work as expected (could be a bug in DOpus5). This was why
@{par}  listers would return to their old paths when iconified after a WinCopy
@{par}  or WinSwap.
@{par}
@{par}@{u}@{fg shine} v1.6 - 6-Jan-1996 @{uu}
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} @{b}Added@{ub} and then @{b}Removed@{ub} @{fg fill}ReScan@{fg text} command - it didn't do what was wanted.
@{par}  (@{" Thanks " LINK Credits} anyway to @{b}Peter Schulz@{ub} for the idea, sorry it didn't work Peter!)
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} @{bg fill} DirToDest @{bg back} now de-selects the directory before reading it into the
@{par}  destination lister instead of afterwards.
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} @{b}Removed@{ub} section about possible @{fg fill}enforcer hits@{fg text}, they were nothing to
@{par}  do with my programs (YIPEE!).
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} @{b}Updated@{ub} @{" Credits " LINK Credits} section. (Most importantly my @{b}new EMail/WWW addresses@{ub}).
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} @{b}Added@{ub} EMail address and WWW URL for @{" Children of the Storm " LINK COTS_Charity}.
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} This should be the last @{fg fill}DOpusFuncs@{fg text} update before @{fg fill}DOpus 5.5@{fg text} is released.
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} Hey! It's my birthday tomorrow!... :-)
@{par}
@{par}@{u}@{fg shine} v1.7 - 8-Jan-1996 @{uu}
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} Now @{b}requires@{ub} (and checks for) @{fg fill}DOpus v5.5@{fg text} or above.
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} Thanks to @{fg fill}DOpus 5.5@{fg text}, you can now open listers in the @{b}top corner@{ub} of the
@{par}  screen, and you can also open them @{" under the mouse " LINK U_NewPos}.
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} Error routine returns error strings from @{fg fill}DOpus5.5@{fg text} which could help to explain
@{par}  @{i}why @{ui}something went wrong, not just what went wrong (e.g. "@{i}Could not open
@{par}  a new lister, DOpus Reason: Insufficient memory@{ui}", instead of just
@{par}  "@{i}Could not open a new lister@{ui}").
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} One or two other minor improvements.
@{par}
@{par}@{u}@{fg shine} v1.8 - 21-Mar-1996 @{uu}
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} @{" WinSwap " LINK U_WinSwap} now swaps the actual lister windows around instead of their
@{par}  paths (This is the way my original WinSwap.dopus5 worked, but I thought
@{par}  the method was slower in some cases which isn't true. Edmund Vermeulen's
@{par}  SwapListers.dopus5 encouraged me to think again -- Thanks Edmund. :-) ).
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} Debug version no longer included in archive.
@{par}
@{par}@{u}@{fg shine} v1.9 - 30-Mar-1996 @{uu}
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} Added @{bg fill} PathSwap @{bg back} which behaves like the old @{b}WinSwap@{ub} (for locked listers).
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} Added @{" LineClip " LINK U_LineClip} option which tells @{" ClipEntry " LINK U_ClipEntry} to put each filename on
@{par}  a separate line. Requested by Georges Goncalves -- Thanks Georges!
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} Added commands to @{" close all listers " LINK U_LCloseAll} and @{" iconify all listers " LINK U_LIconAll}.
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} Note my new @{" webpage URL " LINK Credits}.
@{par}
@{bg fill}===========================================================================@{bg back}
@{par}
@{par}@{u}@{fg shine} v2.0 - 11-May-1996 @{uu}
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} The way the program works has been rationalised some what. Hopefully it's
@{par}  now simpler to use and more like the internal commands of Opus. The
@{par}  program is probably not quite as powerful as before, but I hope noone
@{par}  will notice -- if something is missing just let me know and I'll make it
@{par}  possible again.
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} Openning new listers is much quicker now -- It's done the right way now,
@{par}  instead of the lazy method I used before to save myself 15 minutes of
@{par}  code time or something stupid. If you have a slower machine, please
@{par}  read the @{" bugs " LINK Future} section.
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} @{bg fill} ParentToDest @{bg back} has been renamed to @{" ScanParent " LINK U_ScanParent} in keeping with DOpus
@{par}  function names and to reflect that fact that it defaults to a new lister.
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} @{" WinSwap " LINK U_WinSwap} now checks for locked listers and does a path-swap automatically
@{par}  if it detects it can't move one of them. The separate @{bg fill} PathSwap @{bg back} command is
@{par}  gone.
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} @{" ScanParent " LINK U_ScanParent} and @{" WinCopy " LINK U_WinCopy} now behave more like the internal DOpus
@{par}  functions in that they will default to reading into the destination
@{par}  lister if there is one, creating a new lister if not. You can force
@{par}  them to open a new lister with the @{" New " LINK U_New} switch. The @{bg fill} NoNew @{bg back} switch is
@{par}  gone so it is no longer possible to force an error message instead of
@{par}  creating a new lister when one doesn't exist.
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} The position of any new listers which are openned can be defined with
@{par}  the @{" NewPos " LINK U_NewPos} keyword.
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} @{bg fill} DirToDest @{bg back} is gone as the built-in ScanDir command in DOpus 5.5 can do
@{par}  pretty much the same job. If anyone was using the extra bits offered
@{par}  by DirToDest and wants them back in, let me know.
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} The @{bg fill} NewDest @{bg back}, @{bg fill} DestDir @{bg back}, @{bg fill} DestPos @{bg back}, @{bg fill} DestLock @{bg back} and corresponding Source
@{par}  arguments are gone. You just have the @{" New " LINK U_New} and @{" NewPos " LINK U_NewPos} arguments
@{par}  now, but that's enough control, for me at least. If you want to
@{par}  be able to open a locked-dest lister or something, use @{fg shine}CDOpus@{fg text}.
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} The @{bg fill} ToFront @{bg back} switch is gone and DOpus is never brought to the front.
@{par}  (Presumably it never needs to be seeing as DOpusFuncs is run from
@{par}  DOpus buttons, or at least intended to be).
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} The @{bg fill} Index @{bg back} for this guide is gone. I doubt anyone ever used it for
@{par}  such a small program.
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} DOpusFuncs now chooses to silently fail in certain situations which used
@{par}  to result in annoying error requesters. For example, if you try to do
@{par}  a @{" WinSwap " LINK U_WinSwap} without a source lister, nothing will happen and you will not
@{par}  get an error message. I find this preferable and it's more like Opus,
@{par}  once again.
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} Tidied up the AmigaGuide.
@{par}
@{par}@{u}@{fg shine} v2.1 - 15-May-1996 @{uu}
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} The @{" PathSwap " LINK U_PathSwap} switch is back. Frederic Steinfels had a use for it
@{par}  which I hadn't considered, @{i}thanks Fred! @{ui}

@Remark VERSION NUMBERS/DATES: VER string and Contents Node.

@ENDNODE
@NODE Future "DOpusFuncs - Future & Known Bugs"

@{par}See also: @{" History " LINK History}
@{par}          @{" Credits " LINK Credits}
@{par}
@{par}@{fg shine}@{u} To Do: (well, maybe) @{uu}
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} Turn it into a propper @{fg shine}DOpus5 module@{fg text}. (Need a DOpus5 API)
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} If you want something, @{" ask " LINK Credits} for it!
@{par}
@{par}@{fg shine}@{u} Known Bugs: @{uu}
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} There is a bug in the OS3.1 AmigaGuide which can cause extra spaces,
@{par}  missing spaces, and duplicated words at line-wraps. @{b}This it not my fault!@{ub}
@{par}@{fg fill}o@{fg text} The OS3.1 Autodocs state that there are some bugs in the OS2 version of
@{par}  iffparse.library. If @{" ClipEntry " LINK U_ClipEntry} appears to go bananas and you're using
@{par}  OS2, it @{i}might @{ui}not be my fault. @{bg shine}:-)@{bg back}
